        %h3 Wasting Supplies
        %p Wasting business supplies can be a pervasive type of loss for a company. For example, paper waste can be significant. Instead of circulating hard-copy memorandums among employees, use email to communicate information. Recycle paper or reuse it to make scratch pads. Set printers and copiers to use less ink, and make two-sided copies instead of single-sided copies. Update customer mailing lists to ensure that the list of customers is current. Reuse and recycle boxes and   packaging for shipping.
        %ul
          %li
            %a{:href => "https://www.sba.gov/offices/district/nd/fargo/resources/how-save-cash-start-business"} How to Save Cash to Start a Business
          %li
