        %h3 Wasting Energy
        %p Small businesses can focus on energy usage to cut costs and save   money. Turning off equipment and lights when not in use is an effective way to reduce expenses. Installing newer appliances may save money  because they use less energy. Install a programmable thermostat to control temperatures, which can help reduce heating and cooling costs. Use lower-wattage light bulbs in light fixtures, or install compact fluorescent bulbs instead of incandescent light bulbs.
