            (PDF)
          %li
            %a{:href => "https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2009-11-12/10-ways-to-cut-health-care-costs-right-now"} 10 Ways to Cut Health-Care Costs Right Now
        %h3 Overpaying Taxes
        %p A small-business owner can unwittingly overpay taxes, which can result in significant financial loss for a company. Overlooking tax deductions available to a business owner could result in the overpayment of taxes. Often, a small-business owner might not know about tax deductions and so doesn't take advantage of them when calculating income tax due by the company. Other times, a business owner might not   maintain detailed records of expenses that would enable taking these deductions. Hiring a tax expert or accountant to assist with record-keeping and income taxes can be invaluable for saving money in the long term.
